// Remark Annotations Plugin
// A remark (unified) plugin that parses HTML comment annotation markers in markdown
// and converts them into custom 'annotation' AST nodes for rendering.

Supported patterns (both block and inline/range variants):
  <!-- comment: text -->
  <!-- comment-start: text -->...<!-- comment-end -->
  <!-- status: proposed -->
  <!-- propose-start -->...<!-- propose-end -->
  <!-- status: approved -->
  <!-- approve-start -->...<!-- approve-end -->
  <!-- status: rejected: reason -->
  <!-- reject-start: reason -->...<!-- reject-end -->

FUNCTION annotationNode(type, text, children) -> AnnotationMdastNode
  Construct and return a custom MDAST node of type 'annotation' with the given annotation type,
  optional text (comment text or reject reason), and optional child nodes (for inline ranges).

---

FUNCTION findSibling(parent, startIndex, pattern) -> number | null
  Scan siblings after startIndex for an HTML node matching the pattern.
  Return the index of the first match, or null if not found.

---

FUNCTION remarkAnnotations() -> Plugin                                  EXPORT
  CALLS: annotationNode (remarkAnnotations), findSibling (remarkAnnotations)
  Walk all HTML nodes in the tree.
  For each node, attempt to match it against each annotation pattern in priority order.
  For block patterns (single node): record a transformation replacing just that node.
  For start/end patterns (range): find the matching end node, collect the children between them,
  and record a transformation replacing the start-to-end range with a single annotation node.
  After visiting the full tree, apply all transformations in reverse index order to avoid index shifting.
